  "description": "A P300-based brain-computer interface dataset for home appliance control, comprising EEG recordings from 15 healthy subjects performing a visual oddball task with 31-channel recordings at 500 Hz sampling rate. The dataset includes 50 training and 30 testing trials per subject, with target and non-target stimulus classifications for electric light control applications.",
  "methods_description": "EEG data were acquired using a 31-channel actiCHamp system (Brain Products) at 500 Hz sampling rate with linked mastoid reference. Participants performed a P300 oddball paradigm with visual flash stimuli presented on an LCD display at 750 ms stimulus onset asynchrony. Trial duration was 1.0 second, and visual feedback was provided during online BCI operation.",
